properties.Name: InsuranceCompanyRating
properties.Description:
The Rating Service rating of the Insurer for the associated period of time.

This reflects the strength and financial capabilities of the insurance company as of the associated period of time.

Columns.Name: InsuranceCompanyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Company.

Columns.Name: InsuranceCompanyRatingServiceId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Rating Service.

Columns.Name: RatingId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of a Rating.

Various ratings services have developed their own system for rating insurance companies:

A.M. Best = A-, A, A+, A++, B-,B, B+, B++, C-,C,C+,C++, D,E,F
S&P = AAA,AA,A,BBB,BB,B,CCC,CC,C,D
Moody's = Aaa,Aa,A,Baa,Ba,B,Caa,Ca,C

D&P = AAA,AA+,AA,AA-A+,A,A-,BBB+,BBB,BBB-,BB+,BB,BB-,CCC

Columns.Name: PeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period starting date for which the associated rating applies.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period ending date for which the associated rating applies.

Columns.Name: InsuranceCompanyRatingNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the insurance company rating.
